20:40.369 --> 20:42.676
[ominous music]

20:42.719 --> 20:45.505
[Jerry whimpering]

20:52.294 --> 20:53.164
- I'm so sorry.

20:54.383 --> 20:55.210
I am.

20:55.254 --> 20:57.865
- Oh my God, Jerry.

20:57.908 --> 21:00.128
[footsteps tapping]

21:00.171 --> 21:02.696
[suspenseful music]

21:02.739 --> 21:05.481
[brooding music]

21:09.746 --> 21:11.748
- Even if the PUD had expired,

21:11.792 --> 21:13.837
the regular zoning
laws and fire codes

21:13.881 --> 21:16.623
would not allow the complex
to be built next to the mall.

21:16.666 --> 21:18.015
And from what I've been hearing,

21:18.059 --> 21:19.321
there's a lot of talk

21:19.365 --> 21:20.496
about putting in a
dog park next to us.

21:20.540 --> 21:22.890
So as far as I'm concerned,

21:22.933 --> 21:24.152
Jean, I'm in a meeting.

21:27.982 --> 21:30.854
- Max Kelly, Detective Santiago.

21:32.029 --> 21:33.248
Can I have a word with you?

21:34.205 --> 21:36.077
- Oh, Jean, one minute please.

21:37.600 --> 21:38.427
What's this about?

21:38.471 --> 21:39.298
- Outside.

21:41.169 --> 21:43.911
[dramatic music]

21:45.173 --> 21:47.044
