it was early out today.

21:48.002 --> 21:49.656
Do you wanna talk to her?

21:49.699 --> 21:51.658
She might be willing
to forgive you.

21:53.442 --> 21:55.009
- [Ari] Hi, daddy.

21:55.879 --> 21:57.751
Nah, I knew you forgot.

21:57.794 --> 21:59.143
I'm drawing.

21:59.187 --> 22:01.102
Are you coming to my
cheerleading practice?

22:01.145 --> 22:04.758
You're always working.

22:04.801 --> 22:06.020
Okay, bye daddy.

22:10.807 --> 22:12.940
[group chattering]

22:12.983 --> 22:14.333
- Thank you, Kristy.

22:15.682 --> 22:16.291
Thank you.

22:17.510 --> 22:18.685
Corner's preliminary.

22:19.686 --> 22:20.382
- It's about time.

22:23.385 --> 22:26.170
- Victim one, Dr. Susan Kelly.

22:26.214 --> 22:27.824
Multiple stab wounds.

22:27.868 --> 22:31.654
Second victim was FBI
agent Gerald Kelly.

22:31.698 --> 22:34.222
This guy's brother,
multiple stab wounds,

22:34.265 --> 22:36.398
couple of missing fingers,

22:36.442 --> 22:39.619
other fingers had paper clips
inserted under their nails.

22:42.143 --> 22:44.885
- [Vasquez] This looks
pretty black and white to me.

22:44.928 --> 22:46.756
Daddy comes home early,

22:46.800 --> 22:49.019
finds mommy with the
brother going at it.

22:49.063 --> 22:50.717
It's a crime of passion.

22:53.589 --> 22:57.419
- What we have is
a dead FBI agent.

22:57.463 --> 22:59.639
The feds are gonna take
this over in a heartbeat.

22:59.682 --> 23:00.901
So we've gotta get
outta their way

23:00.944 --> 23:02.468
and focus on finding that child

23:02.511 --> 23:04.339
while we still have
any jurisdiction left.

23:04.383 --> 23:05.819
- This guy's clean.

23:05.862 --> 23:08.256
Someone murdered his family

23:08.299 --> 23:09.866
so why don't we
cut him some slack

23:09.910 --> 23:12.608
and uh, think about it, it
could be one of us in there.

23:16.177 --> 23:18.962
- [Vasquez] How can you
be so sure it wasn't him?

23:20.355 --> 23:22.313
- Because I'm a very
good judge of character.

23:22.357 --> 23:24.664
[Daniels scoffs]

23:24.707 --> 23:26.100
What?

23:26.143 --> 23:27.710
- Let's just say good judgment's

23:27.754 --> 23:29.190
not the first thing
that pops into my head

23:29.233 --> 23:30.844
when I see your pretty face.

23:32.236 --> 23:34.151
- Oh, you wanna go there?

23:34.195 --> 23:35.979
- No.

23:36.023 --> 23:37.416
- I want you to go in
there and talk to this man.

23:38.460 --> 23:41.245
- This guy and I
sat for 12 years

23:41.289 --> 23:43.422
in the same black and white.

23:43.465 --> 23:45.336
We had a coffee together,
had lunch together.

23:46.729 --> 23:49.602
Look at him now, the
big fucking boss.

23:52.213 --> 23:53.083
Sure.

23:58.698 --> 24:01.309
[Daniels sighs]

24:01.352 --> 24:03.180
- Takes a few decades
to get to know him.

24:05.444 --> 24:09.012
[brooding music]

24:09.056 --> 24:11.711
- You and your
brother got arrested

24:13.103 --> 24:14.931
drifting cars in
the parking lot.

24:16.455 --> 24:17.412
The abandoned steam plant.

24:19.980 --> 24:20.894
Joined the Navy.

24:23.592 --> 24:24.463
What happened to you?

24:26.334 --> 24:27.335
Dishonorable discharge.

24:30.338 --> 24:31.252
- It's complicated.

24:34.298 --> 24:35.474
- It always is, isn't it?

24:44.744 --> 24:48.530
Your brother, Agent Kelly
called you at 9:00 PM,

24:50.271 --> 24:51.315
what he'd want?

24:51.359 --> 24:53.840
- I don't know, all right.

24:53.883 --> 24:56.320
He called me, I
couldn't hear anything.

24:56.364 --> 24:58.366
Thought he'd call me
back, but he never did.

24:59.585 --> 25:00.716
- And when you saw
him at the restaurant,

25:00.760 --> 25:02.283
did you recognize
anybody was with him?

25:02.326 --> 25:03.850
- No.

25:03.893 --> 25:05.199
I didn't recognize
anyone with him.

25:06.505 --> 25:07.723
Have you found my daughter yet?

25:10.421 --> 25:11.684
- We're knocking on every door.

25:13.773 --> 25:15.296
We're also searching
all over Discovery Park

25:15.339 --> 25:17.037
an Lincoln Park.

25:17.080 --> 25:19.779
We have to plan for
any possible scenario.

25:24.305 --> 25:26.307
Look, I got two kids of my own,

25:26.350 --> 25:29.136
so it could be me
in your situation.

25:31.138 --> 25:33.314
Trust me when I
tell you that I'm,

25:33.357 --> 25:34.924
I care and I'm
gonna do everything

25:34.968 --> 25:36.535
I can to find your daughter.

25:48.198 --> 25:49.112
- What are they like?

25:50.984 --> 25:51.854
- Who?

25:53.726 --> 25:54.770
- Your, your kids?

25:59.383 --> 26:00.428
- [sighs] I don't know.

26:02.212 --> 26:03.605
Typical teenagers, I guess.

26:06.869 --> 26:08.088
Don't get to see them much.

26:10.960 --> 26:11.787
Probably my fault.

26:13.876 --> 26:15.182
Having trouble with the Mrs.

26:18.272 --> 26:22.798
But when we're together, it's
all, all good quality time.

26:27.542 --> 26:30.197
- Should have been all quantity.

26:31.285 --> 26:31.981
- [Santiago] What?

26:35.115 --> 26:39.032
- Any time you spend with
your child is quality time.

26:41.774 --> 26:44.559
What would you do
if you were me?

26:47.301 --> 26:48.607
- [Santiago] How do you mean?

26:51.000 --> 26:53.960
- If you found out
someone murdered,

26:54.003 --> 26:58.660
murdered your whole
family, what would you do?

27:01.532 --> 27:05.536
- Oh, uh, buddy, I'm,
I'm the wrong guy to ask.

27:06.494 --> 27:10.324
- What would you do?

27:12.369 --> 27:14.154
- Well

27:18.288 --> 27:19.768
I'm a simple man

27:21.988 --> 27:25.687
and so I probably would
put them on a chair.

27:27.297 --> 27:28.255
- Oh, shit.

27:32.346 --> 27:35.828
- And then I would wack them
with one of them nail bats.

27:37.438 --> 27:38.569
You know, the ones
with the nails

27:38.613 --> 27:40.136
and the barbed wire all over.

27:44.401 --> 27:46.708
Then I would swing
until my arms fell off.

27:48.536 --> 27:49.755
I can't even think
about that shit

27:49.798 --> 27:52.540
without getting my
fucking blood boiling.

27:52.583 --> 27:56.370
But fucking monsters
don't get a second chance

27:58.546 --> 28:00.287
because they will do it again.

28:02.289 --> 28:04.857
[door clicks]

28:04.900 --> 28:07.642
[door bangs]

28:07.686 --> 28:08.948
- [Daniels] Detective Santiago,

28:08.991 --> 28:10.645
may I have a word with
you outside please.

28:20.960 --> 28:23.092
Mr. Kelly, I'm so
sorry about that.

28:23.136 --> 28:26.617
That is not a reflection on
this department in any way.

28:26.661 --> 28:28.532
- [Max] Look, I can't
sit here anymore.

28:28.576 --> 28:29.751
- Well, you can't go home.

28:29.795 --> 28:32.101
Your house is a crime
scene right now.

28:32.145 --> 28:33.799
You'd be better off
staying here with us.

28:34.887 --> 28:35.714
- Am I free to go?

28:37.411 --> 28:39.587
- [Daniels] Yes,
of course you are.

28:39.630 --> 28:41.023
Where are you going?

28:43.069 --> 28:45.724
[ominous music]

28:47.116 --> 28:51.599
[birds chirping]
[group chattering]

28:52.469 --> 28:54.776
[Max crying]

29:05.744 --> 29:08.398
[ominous music]

29:41.344 --> 29:43.694
[Max crying]

29:52.181 --> 29:54.575
